{"url": "https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/a9995872/amal-clooney-magnificent-mother/", "text": "The Venice Film Festival is official underway, and the Clooneys wasted no time in arriving. Of course, the family didn\u2019t have far to travel, given that they own a house, called Villa Oleandra (and estimated to be worth around $100 million), in Italy, along the coast of Lake Como. To celebrate the annual festival a little early, the Clooneys hosted a small but very starry soir\u00e9e at their home.\n\nIt was quite the Hollywood affair, with the family being joined by famous friends like Adam Sandler, Laura Dern, Jim Broadbent, Shailene Woodley, Greta Gerwig and her husband, and fellow filmmaker Noah Baumbach\u2014guests who will likely attend the film festival as well.\n\nBut the most surprising guests at George and Amal\u2019s f\u00eate were their eight year-old twins, Ella and Alexander, who are rarely seen in public. The little Clooneys were captured in a series of photos that have since been deleted (which makes sense given that the parents are very private about their family life). \u201cWe don\u2019t put our children out there; we\u2019ve never put their photo out there or anything like that,\u201d Amal told Glamour this past July.\n\nJacopo Raule // Getty Images The Clooneys are seen arriving at the Venice Film Festival, after hosting people at their Lake Como villa.\n\nBut for the outing, Amal chose a summery white dress, which she accessorized with a large straw hat featuring a rope band detail. Meanwhile, George chose a navy blue tee, which he paired with matching slacks and sunglasses.\n\nTheir kids looked like the picture of posh Italian style too. Ella wore a denim minidress and blue crossbody, while Alexander sported a blue pinstripe top and white linen shorts.\n\nEarlier this year, George sat down for an interview with Gayle King for CBS Mornings, where he raved about his children. \u201cThe kids are seven, about to be eight, which is a pretty great age. They\u2019re really curious and funny ... and make us laugh.\u201d\n\nHe also gave a shoutout to his wife, saying: \u201cAmal and I are having a really great time in life. We were here with you once before and I remember we said we\u2019d never had an argument; we still haven\u2019t.\u201d He jokingly added, \u201cWe\u2019re trying to find something to fight about.\u201d\n\nBack in July, Amal also gushed about George, saying: \u201cI have a partner in life who is so supportive of what I do. So I don\u2019t feel like I have to apologize for it or rein it in.\u201d", "images": ["https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/george-clooney-and-amal-clooney-attend-the-clooney-news-photo-1763319329.pjpeg?crop=0.668xw:1.00xh;0.167xw,0&resize=360:*", "https://www.harpersbazaar.com/_assets/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/social/youtube.ce3e1ae.svg?primary=%2523000000&id=social-button-icon", "https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/mormon-wives-s3-vertical-2700x4000-pre-69161bf6c5647.jpg?crop=0.821xw:0.554xh;0.120xw,0.313xh&resize=360:*", "https://www.harpersbazaar.com/_assets/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/search.f1c199c.svg", "https://www.harpersbazaar.com/_assets/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/x-regular.e414d97.svg", "https://www.harpersbazaar.com/_assets/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/social/instagram.f282b14.svg?primary=%2523000000&id=social-button-icon", "https://www.harpersbazaar.com/_assets/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/play.db7c035.svg?primary=%2523ffffff", "https://www.harpersbazaar.com/_assets/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/social/facebook.a5a3a69.svg?primary=%2523000000&id=social-button-icon", "https://www.harpersbazaar.com/_assets/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/caret-left-regular.5546078.svg", "https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/bgus-3397134-001-1-68ffbaa3768ef.jpg?crop=0.848xw:0.557xh;0.130xw,0.101xh&resize=360:*", "https://www.harpersbazaar.com/_assets/design-tokens/harpersbazaar/static/images/logos/logo.823d7af.svg?primary=%2523fffff